  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "Currently, both functions have return values in their signatures:\r\n\r\n```\r\nfunction mint(address _to, uint256 _amount) onlyOwner canMint returns (bool) {\r\nfunction finishMinting() onlyOwner returns (bool) {\r\n```\r\n\r\nwhich is inconsistent with the general approach used in this repo to prefer fail-fast error handling with throwing. Moreover, the comment suggests:\r\n\r\n`* @return A boolean that indicates if the operation was successful.`\r\n\r\nthat the operation may return false which is never the case.\r\n\r\nMaybe it's better to strip this return values or is there any reasoning behind them that I'm missing?",
