    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Thx for the answer @frangio !\r\nBoth of the issues refer to [ERC-20](https://github.com/ethereum/EIPs/issues/20) interface and the mentioned functions are out of the scope of the reference so it won't break any compatibility requirements. Moreover, the main argument for return values is to save gas costs for users by returning `false` while the methods never return `false` but throw exception consuming all of the gas. In other words, the current implementation neither follows return pattern by being able to return `false` nor have a simple signature without return values.\r\nPlease, let me know if you see my point in here?",
