    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "I do see your point! I understand this isn't about ERC20 compatibility, but consistency within the OpenZeppelin framework.\r\n\r\nIt's also true that the return values are basically unused because methods throw on error. This is actually similar to what is suggested in ERC20, for example in the description of `transfer`:\r\n> The function SHOULD throw if the `_from` account balance has not enough tokens to spend.\r\nIt's odd behavior, yes...\r\n\r\nIn any case, we're going to add back return values to our ERC20 tokens, so MintableToken will keep them in the spirit of consistency.\r\n\r\nThanks for bringing this up @jakub-wojciechowski!",
